In this article, President Obama commemorates the ninth anniversary of the September 11 attacks by declaring a National Day of Service and Remembrance. He emphasizes that the United States is a nation united by common ideals. He acknowledges the pain and loss that still remains from the attacks and expresses sympathy for the families of the victims. The President pays tribute to the firefighters, first responders, and military personnel who sacrificed their lives to protect others. He highlights the importance of unity and the capacity for good in times of tragedy. President Obama reaffirms the nation's commitment to defending the country and expresses gratitude to the soldiers and their families. He concludes by emphasizing the need to come together as a community and serve those in need, as a way to honor the shared ideals of the nation.